TITLE: Norway nightclub shooting: 2 dead, 10 injured in suspected terror-linked attack
SUMMARY: A mass shooting at a Norway nightclub and the surrounding area that left two dead and 10 injured is being investigated as a suspected terrorist-linked attack. It happened during Oslo's Pride festival.

TITLE: Top Gun Ukrainian pilots push US for jets, senator says lawmakers will 'press the case' with White House
SUMMARY: Two Ukrainian fighter pilots traveled to Washington to urge lawmakers to help them obtain more advanced air defense systems and modern warplanes as the fight against Russia continues.

TITLE: Afghanistan earthquake death toll rises to 1,150 following aftershock
SUMMARY: Five more people died in Afghanistan when an aftershock struck an area already rattled by an earthquake that killed more than 1,000 people.

TITLE: UN agency teachers urge terrorism and murder of Jews, report claims
SUMMARY: UN Watch, a Swiss based NGO issued a report, Thursday, that uncovered a shocking picture of how some teachers who work for UNRWA put out explicit and violent messages on social media aimed against Israel and Jews.

TITLE: Ukrainian forces retreating from eastern city Sievierodonetsk to avoid being encircled by Russians
SUMMARY: Ukrainian forces have retreated from a city in eastern Ukraine over fears they could be encircled by Russian troops.

TITLE: Boris Johnson under pressure: UK's Conservative Party loses 2 parliamentary seats
SUMMARY: UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party lost two parliamentary seats on Friday, causing the party's chairman to resign.

TITLE: Ukraine receives long-range rocket system; Russian official threatens strike on US embassy in Kyiv
SUMMARY: High Mobility Artillery Rocket Systems arrived in Ukraine this week, prompting the Ukrainian Defense Minister to thank the U.S. 'for these powerful tools.'

TITLE: What to know: Jesuit priests killed in Sierra Tarahumara, Mexico
SUMMARY: Two Jesuit priests were killed in northern Mexico this week. The shooter was following a tourist guide when he entered the church and killed the two priests and the guide.

TITLE: Ukraine lands victory in EU vote on candidate status
SUMMARY: Leaders from the European Union voted Thursday to allow Ukraine candidate status in its first major step forward in joining the 27-member alliance.

TITLE: Austria scraps compulsory COVID-19 vaccination, measure was suspended in March
SUMMARY: Austria voted to drop its mandatory coronavirus vaccine mandate, saying it's unlikely to raise one of Europe's lowest vaccination rates, said the Austrian health minister.

TITLE: US to send $450M in rocket systems, other aid to Ukraine: officials
SUMMARY: U.S. officials announced that they will send additional military aid to help Ukraine in their war against Russia. This comes just one day after Ukrainian pilots pleaded for more help.

TITLE: UK court says widower can use late wife's frozen embryo for surrogate
SUMMARY: A U.K. High Court ruled in favor of a widower who was denied a request to use his late wife's frozen embryos with a surrogate due to her not having given written consent.

TITLE: Ukraine's Zelenskyy calls for 'fair tribunal' in Nuremberg-style trials to hold Russia accountable
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenksyy called for a 'fair tribunal' to hol Russian war criminals accountable under Nuremberg-style trials.

TITLE: Okinawa, Japan pushes US to draw down base presence 77 years after battle's end
SUMMARY: The 77th anniversary of Okinawa prompted Japan's governor to minimize the presence of U.S. military in south Japan. The Battle of Okinawa killed almost 200,000 people at the time.

TITLE: Pope Francis says resigning 'does not cross his mind' amid health struggles
SUMMARY: Pope Francis quashed rumors of an impending resignation from the papacy after reportedly telling a Brazilian archbishop that he had no plans to step down.

TITLE: Bookmakers favor Asian or Black successor to Pope Francis
SUMMARY: Bookmakers believe that a Black or Asian cardinal would be most likely to replace Pope Francis if he were to resign, a reality some observers say is unlikely.

TITLE: French court bans burkinis, doesn't block city allowing topless women in public swim areas
SUMMARY: France's highest administrative court, the Council of State, overturned a lower court decision allowing "burkini" swimwear at public pools and beaches.

TITLE: Afghanistan earthquake kills at least 1,000 people, officials say
SUMMARY: A magnitude 6 earthquake in eastern Afghanistan killed at least 1,000 people Wednesday morning. The earthquakeâ€™s tremors were felt over 310 miles by 119 million people across the country.

TITLE: Pope shocked by killing of Jesuit priests in Mexico
SUMMARY: Pope Francis expressed his shock over the killings of two Jesuit priests and a lay person in Mexico along with condemning the ongoing violence in the country.

TITLE: Cocaine dealer identified thanks to Conor McGregor mural sentenced to 29 years for drug trafficking
SUMMARY: Ryan Palin was convicted of drug charges after police tracked him down thanks to a mural of Connor McGregor that they recognized was painted on a wall in his home.
